meanings.sent1: The church bells outringing the birdsong echoed through the valley.
meanings.sent2: Her laughter outringing the chatter of the crowd.
meanings.sent3: The alarm clock tried to outringing the rooster's crow, but failed miserably.
meanings.sent4: His voice outringing the thunderstorm, commanding attention from all.
meanings.sent5: The cheers of the fans outringing the referee's whistle, signaling victory.

meanings.definition: To sound louder than something else
meanings.sent1: The fireworks outringing the distant car horns on New Year's Eve.
meanings.sent2: The music from the party next door outringing the quiet of the night.
meanings.sent3: The toddler's tantrum outringing the noise of the busy street.
meanings.sent4: Her sobs outringing the gentle rain tapping on the window.
meanings.sent5: The roar of the waterfall outringing all other sounds in the forest.
